<div>

	<h3>What is Best Future Forests?</h3>

    <p>A transformative initiative aimed at digitalizing forest resource management and tree improvement in Alberta, Canada.</p>
    <p>The project seeks to integrate high-throughput genotyping, predictive analytics, and decision-making science to ensure responsible stewardship of forest genetic resources in the face of climate challenges, and the growing demand for sustainable forest ecosystems and products.</p>
    <p>This is a joint effort across the Government of Alberta (GoA), forest industry partners of Tree Improvement of Alberta, University of Alberta (UofA, CA), and Oklahoma State University (USA).</p>

	<h3>How can I use the database?</h3>

  Best Future Forests is a comprehensive breeding management and analysis software, that only requires a browser.
  It can be used to design field layouts, collect phenotypic information using tablets, support the collection of genotyping
  samples in a field, store large amounts of high density genotypic information, and provide Genomic Selection related analyses
  and predictions. Best Future Forests supports the <a href="https://brapi.org/specification">BrAPI</a> standard.

  <h3>How can I learn more?</h3>

  See the <a href="/about">About</a> page for more information including tutorials and manuals.
</div>

